<div id="review_163057235" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/163057235" />
    <a title="Patrick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/922495-patrick"><img alt="Patrick" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1351307095p2/922495.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/163057235?book_show_action=true">Apr 23, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Patrick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Patrick" href="/user/show/922495-patrick">Patrick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer163057235" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8593553065447737828">When I started reading this, I had the vague expectation that it was going to be some sort of urban fantasy. <br/><br/>It wasn&apos;t. But that didn&apos;t keep me absolutely loving it. <br/><br/>It&apos;s funny, clever, fast-moving, irreverent, and horrifying in turns. I highly recommend it. Unless you&apos;re a hypochondriac. If you are, you should avoid it like the plague. (heh.) <br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText8593553065447737828" style="display:none">When I started reading this, I had the vague expectation that it was going to be some sort of urban fantasy. <br /><br />It wasn't. But that didn't keep me absolutely loving it. <br /><br />It's funny, clever, fast-moving, irreverent, and horrifying in turns. I highly recommend it. Unless you're a hypochondriac. If you are, you should avoid it like the plague. (heh.) <br /><br /></span>
