<div id="review_2204216582" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2204216582" />
    <a title="Jane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39215947-jane"><img alt="Jane" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1526919066p2/39215947.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2204216582?book_show_action=true">Dec 04, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jane" href="/user/show/39215947-jane">Jane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39215947-jane?shelf=z2017">z2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39215947-jane?shelf=1audio">1audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39215947-jane?shelf=audio-read">audio-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2204216582" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2984707442829981217">3.5 stars for the Audible version.<br/><br/>Well, now. I&apos;m not even really sure what I just finished listening to! <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3173125.Beat_the_Reaper__Peter_Brown__1_' title='Beat the Reaper (Peter Brown #1) by Josh Bazell' rel='nofollow noopener'>Beat the Reaper</a> was fast-paced, gritty, edgy, and funny. It also, at times, seemed to try too hard to be shocking. This is not a book for prudes nor for the squeamish. <br/><br/>It took me a bit to get into the rhythm of chapters that alternated between telling past events and those happening *right now*, but overall I enjoyed this book, and I think narrator <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2889695.Robert_Petkoff' title='Robert Petkoff' rel='nofollow noopener'>Robert Petkoff</a> was a perfect choice -- I&apos;ll </span>
  <span id="freeText2984707442829981217" style="display:none">3.5 stars for the Audible version.<br /><br />Well, now. I'm not even really sure what I just finished listening to! <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3173125.Beat_the_Reaper__Peter_Brown__1_" title="Beat the Reaper (Peter Brown #1) by Josh Bazell" rel="nofollow noopener">Beat the Reaper</a> was fast-paced, gritty, edgy, and funny. It also, at times, seemed to try too hard to be shocking. This is not a book for prudes nor for the squeamish. <br /><br />It took me a bit to get into the rhythm of chapters that alternated between telling past events and those happening *right now*, but overall I enjoyed this book, and I think narrator <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2889695.Robert_Petkoff" title="Robert Petkoff" rel="nofollow noopener">Robert Petkoff</a> was a perfect choice -- I'll definitely be looking for more of his work! Unfortunately, I found the music and sound effects, which seemed to have been added almost randomly, to be distracting. It's a shame, too, because the echoing voice effect was perfect when it was used, but other effects were less subtle, and every time the music started up it pulled me right out of the story.<br /><br />I might consider giving the sequel a go despite its less than stellar reviews, but I won't be rushing out to get it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2984707442829981217" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


